          %h1
            Find & Stay Connected to Museums You Love
          %p.intro
            KiwiJar is an app that allows people to find & connect with museums that will interest them. My role in this project was to bring it to life with design, adding in tons of user experience ideas along the way.

  %section.individual-case-study-header.kiwijar

  %section
    .container
      .row
        .col-md-8.col-md-offset-2
          :markdown
            Sometimes when you visit a new place it’s the unexpected gems that you stumble upon that give you the best experiences. Sure, you saw the National Gallery of Art & Design but who’d have thought the Museum of Bad Art (yes that’s the best, worst art) would turn out to be far more entertaining and memorable?

            There are so many Museums in the world that unless you either get lucky or have some insider information you will probably never visit. This is largely because these smaller museums simply don’t have the budget or resources to manage a successful online presence.

            This is what Luis Vazquez of KiwiJar has set out to change. KiwiJar’s aim is to level the playing field for museums, helping the smaller ones get noticed while giving more choice to the general public.
