      .row
        .col-md-12
          %img{alt: "KiwiJar landing page", src: "/images/case-studies/kiwijar/kiwijar-landing-page-full.png"}/
      .row
        .col-md-8.col-md-offset-2
          %h2
            Embracing Personalities
          %p
            One of the main features of KiwiJar is the ability to sort Museums and interests into Jars (aka groups). We have 8 Jars in total which covers pretty much every type of museum we have come across from Art Lovers to Unique People.
      .row
        .col-md-12
          %img{alt: "KiwiJar categories", src: "/images/case-studies/kiwijar/kiwijar-categories.png"}/
      .row
        .col-md-8.col-md-offset-2
          %p
            Because people are more complex than that, we wanted to find a visual way to embrace the differet personalities of everyone on the website. This is why we have made everyones avatar automatically show the colours of the Jars they have selected as their interests.
      .row
        .col-md-12
          %img{alt: "KiwiJar avatars", src: "/images/case-studies/kiwijar/kiwijar-avatars.png"}/
      .row
        .col-md-8.col-md-offset-2
          %p
            This means you can see at a glance what people are interested in and also gives people a slightly different take on the traditional avatar.

  %section.page-section-medium
    .container
      .row
        .col-md-8.col-md-offset-2
          %h2
            Encouraging Exploration
          %p
            KiwiJar is an app that is meant to be played with. It needed to be easy for people to not only find something very specific but also to keep exploring and finding some interesting places they may never have come across before.
      .row
        .col-md-12
          %img{alt: "KiwiJar users", src: "/images/case-studies/kiwijar/kiwijar-users.png"}/

  %section.page-section-large
    .container
      .row
        .col-md-8.col-md-offset-2
          %h2
            Helping Museums Prosper
          %p
            We also had another aim with this web app. Not only did we want to help people find and connect with Museums they’d enjoy but we wanted to help level the playing field for smaller museums. Giving them an online presence will allow them to reach a wider audience while keeping costs down (as they won’t need to build and manage their own websites).
      .row
        .col-md-12
          %img{alt: "KiwiJar museum", src: "/images/case-studies/kiwijar/kiwijar-museum.png"}/

  %section.page-section-medium
    .container
      .row
        .col-md-8.col-md-offset-2
          %h2
            The dashboard has 3 simple goals:
          %ol
            %li
              %span
                A quick at a glance view to see how well the museum is doing during a particular timeframe. This breaks down into profile views, reviews, visits and wish lists so the museum can learn how well they perform during different times of year and during different events.
            %li
              %span
                Reply to reviews quickly and easily. The most recent reviews can be seen right on the dashboard with a field for replying back right there. This means there is no need to load another page just to reply so no time is wasted.
            %li
              %span
                Add events and exhibits. Museums need to show people what they have going on at the moment and what is upcoming. They can add these events from the dashboard.
      .row
        .col-md-12
          %img{alt: "KiwiJar dashboard", src: "/images/case-studies/kiwijar/kiwijar-dashboard.png"}/
